Step 1: Identify the relevant amounts.
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 116257.19  
• Net Profit = 963263.19  

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio using the formula:  
  Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Net Profit)

Step 3: Plug in the values:  
  Ratio = 116257.19 / 963263.19 ≈ 0.1207

Step 4: Rounding the result to two decimal places, we get 0.12.

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is "0.12".
